Cli%3EIvan%20Leong%20won%20a%20%241%20million%20lottery%20when%20he%20was%2023.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20years%20of%20comfortable%20insurance%20work%2C%20he%20quit%20to%20open%20his%20own%20Cantonese%20roast%20pork%20eatery.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EEight%20years%20on%2C%20he's%20rethinking%20his%20choice%20of%20laboring%20behind%20a%20hot%20oven%20and%20working%2011-hour%20days.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIvan%20Leong%2C%2037%2C%20used%20to%20work%20as%20an%20insurance%20agent%20%E2%80%94%20a%20job%20with%20crisp%20button-ups%2C%20perfume%2C%20coffee%20chats%2C%20and%20flexible%20schedules.%20Ten%20years%20later%2C%20as%20he%20slices%20up%20juicy%20pork%20in%20his%20own%20Cantonese%20roast%20pork%20stall%2C%20he%20said%20that%20his%20life%20now%20is%20a%20far%20cry%20from%20what%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELeong%20started%20out%20as%20an%20administrative%20assistant%20at%20a%20recruitment%20firm%2C%20a%20job%20he%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bstagnant.%26quot%3B%20One%20day%20in%202013%2C%20his%20colleagues%20persuaded%20him%20to%20join%20them%20in%20buying%20lottery%20tickets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20a%20stroke%20of%20luck%2C%20the%20lottery%20ticket%20he%20bought%20with%2010%20Singapore%20dollars%20won%20him%20SG%241%20million.%20The%20sudden%20windfall%20gave%20him%20the%20confidence%20to%20quit%20his%20job%2C%20and%20he%20gave%20his%20one-month%20notice%20shortly%20after.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20first%20order%20of%20business%20was%20buying%20a%20government-subsidized%20apartment%20with%20his%20fianc%C3%A9.%20Even%20with%20the%20lottery%20money%2C%20buying%20a%20condominium%20or%20private%20property%20was%20out%20of%20the%20question%2C%20he%20said%2C%20as%20was%20retiring%20early.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHonestly%2C%20one%20million%20is%20never%20enough%2C%20especially%20in%20Singapore%2C%26quot%3B%20Leong%20said.%20Singapore%2C%20a%20tiny%20island%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingapore-millennial-housing-prices-income-debt-dreams-2023-6%23the-typical-singaporean-millennial-earns-between-sg53400-and-sg81900-a-year-but-its-barely-enough-to-stay-afloat-in-one-of-the-worlds-most-expensive-cities-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone%20of%20the%20world's%20most%20expensive%20cities.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20after%20trying%20his%20hand%20at%20selling%20insurance%20products%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20Leong%20felt%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20build%20something%20of%20his%20own%20and%20be%20his%20own%20boss%20for%20a%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20Singapore%2C%20if%20you%20start%20an%20F%26amp%3BB%20business%2C%20you%20can%20be%20a%20boss%20straight%20away.%20It's%20the%20fastest%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20with%20a%20laugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20he%20loved%20cooking%20as%20a%20kid%2C%20particularly%20during%20Lunar%20New%20Year.%20To%20get%20back%20into%20it%2C%20he%20cut%20his%20teeth%20at%20his%20friend's%20roast%20pork%20shop%20in%20Singapore's%20Ang%20Mo%20Kio%20neighborhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20opened%20their%20own%20roast%20pork%2C%20or%20char%20siu%2C%20shop%20in%20Bukit%20Merah%2C%20a%20residential%20area%20in%20the%20south%20of%20Singapore.%20Over%20the%20next%20few%20years%2C%20he%20would%20close%20his%20original%20outlet%20and%20open%20two%20others%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eone%20in%20Woodlands%20and%20another%20in%20Ang%20Mo%20Kio%2C%20both%20of%20which%20are%20residential%20districts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20he%20easily%20spends%2011%20to%2012%20hours%20behind%20the%20counter%20daily.%20Feeding%20a%20hungry%20lunch%20crowd%20means%20reaching%20his%20stall%20at%207%20a.m.%20daily%2C%20and%20he%20rarely%20leaves%20before%206%20p.m.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd11ebee-c038-44f0-84c0-363ec2e7fe0e%5C%22%3EThe%20roast%20pork%20in%20question%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223704%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20trio%20dish%20from%20Char%20Siu%20Lang.%