om%20Alison%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20Meta's%20head%20of%20Facebook%20%E2%80%94%20were%20presented%20in%20court%20this%20week%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-meta-antitrust-trial-testimony-hours-witness-stand-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFTC's%20antitrust%20trial%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMeta%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20main%20topic%20of%20the%20email%20exchange%3A%20How%20to%20keep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFacebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20relevant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20though%20the%20FB%20app's%20engagement%20is%20steady%20in%20many%20places%2C%20it%20feels%20like%20its%20cultural%20relevance%20is%20decreasing%20quickly%20and%20I%20worry%20that%20this%20may%20be%20a%20leading%20indicator%20of%20future%20health%20issues%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20even%20if%20Instagram%20and%20WhatsApp%20did%20well%2C%20he%20didn't%20see%20a%20path%20to%20success%20for%20Meta%20if%20Facebook%20faltered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20months%20before%20these%20emails%2C%20Facebook%20had%20widely%20rolled%20out%20reels%2C%20its%20short-form%20video%20product%20resembling%20TikTok.%20While%20Zuckerberg%20said%20in%20the%20emails%20that%20he%20agreed%20with%20Facebook's%20recent%20shift%20of%20resources%20to%20reels%2C%20he%20wanted%20to%20%26quot%3Bmake%20sure%20we%20have%20a%20unique%20vision%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20Facebook%20app.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20was%20going%20wrong%20on%20Facebook%2C%20then%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20emails%2C%20here's%20what%20was%20affecting%20Facebook's%20cultural%20relevance%20at%20the%20time%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFacebook's%20classic%20act%20of%20%26quot%3Bfriending%26quot%3B%20someone%20seemed%20to%20have%20lost%20its%20luster.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BFirst%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people's%20friend%20graphs%20are%20stale%20and%20not%20filled%20with%20the%20people%20they%20want%20to%20hear%20from%20or%20connect%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20act%20of%20friending%20someone%20also%20felt%20too%20%26quot%3Bheavyweight%26quot%3B%20for%20users.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20want%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20someone%20adding%20friends%20on%20FB%2C%20or%20would%20you%20rather%20be%20seen%20adding%20the%20person%20on%20IG%3F%26quot%3B%20In%20the%20same%20exchange%2C%20Zuckerberg%20presented%20three%20options%20to%20Alison%20that%20could%20help%20Facebook's%20relevancy%2C%20including%20one%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-testify-meta-antitrust-trial-federal-trade-commission-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrazy%20idea%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20of%20wiping%20people's%20friend%20graphs%20and%20having%20them%20start%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20were%20turning%20to%20other%20platforms%2C%20like%20Instagram%2C%20to%20follow%20friends%20and%20public%20figures.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EZuckerberg%20himself%20even%20admitted%20that%20he%20was%20more%20likely%20to%20follow%20surfers%20or%20MMA%20fighters%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finstagram%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Twitter.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20other%20modern%20social%20network%20is%20built%20on%20following%20rather%20than%20friending%2C%20so%20it%20seems%20possible%20that%20the%20FB%20app%20is%20just%20outdated%20because%20it%20never%20adopted%20this%20fundamental%20innovation%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFacebook's%20attempt%20to%20focus%20on%20communities%20with%20groups%20still%20needed%20work.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20optimistic%20about%20community%20messaging%2C%20but%20after%20running%20at%20groups%20in%20FB%20for%20several%20years%2C%20I'm%20not%20sure%20how%20much%20further%20we'll%20be%20able%20to%20push%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20possible%20groups%20will%20just%20never%20be%20as%20big%20as%20friending%2Ffollowing%2C%20and%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20group%20behavior%20is%20moving%20to%20messaging%20anyway.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIts%20push%20into%20short-form%20video%20needed%20to%20feel%20more%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-reveals-decline-friend-content-instagram-facebook-amid-ftc-trial-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3Esocial%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%2C%20and%20also%20unique%20to%20Facebook.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EZuckerberg%20said%20that%20while%20Facebook's%20push%20of%20reels%20was%20good%20for%20surfacing%20interesting%20content%20in%20the%20feed%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20reduces%20the%20social%20sense%20of%20feeling%20connected%20to%20the%20person%20creating%20the%20content%2C%26quot%3B%20especially%20if%20it%20wasn't%20made%20on%20Facebook.%20Alison%20responded%20to%20Zuckerberg%20in%20one%20email%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bproblem%20with%20Facebook%20is%20that%20we%20don't%20have%20a%20culturally%20relevant%20public%20content%20ecosystem%20as%20a%20baseline%20since%20it's%20mainly%20comprised%20of%20commoditized%20news%20and%20video%20publisher%20content.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EFacebook%20has%20a%20litany%20of%20competitors%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0even%20its%20own%20sibling%2C%20Instagram.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20TikTok%2C%20YouTube%2C%20Twitter%2C%20and%20Reddit%20all%20came%20up%20in%20the%20exchange.%20Smaller%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffounders-disrupting-social-media-networking-landscape-new-apps-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20apps%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20also%20referenced%2C%20like%20friend-sharing%20apps%20BeReal%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-instagram-hires-core-team-buzzy-social-media-app-poparazzi-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPoparazzi%3C%2Fa%3E.%20But%20one%20of%20the%20most%20interesting%20competitors%20was%20Instagram%2C%20especially%20since%20its%20acquisition%20by%20Facebook%20is%20core%20to%20the%20FTC's%20case%20against%20Meta.%20(It%20appears%20that%20Instagram's%20top%20exec%2C%20Adam%20Mosseri%2C%20was%20cc'd%20on%20these%20emails.)%20%26quot%3BDifferentiating%20between%20IG%20and%20FB%20is%20important%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20need%20to%20find%20a%20strategy%20that%20doesn't%20leave%20one%20service%20picking%20up%20the%20scraps%20the%20other%20service%20leaves%20behind%20or%20having%20either%20service%20artificially%20or%20unreasonably%20constrain%20itself%2C%26quot%3B%20Zuckerberg%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BRight%20now%20IG%20is%20doing%20well%20on%20cultural%20relevance%20and%20FB%20isn't%2C%20so%20I'm%20more%20focused%20on%20figuring%20out%20a%20reasonable%20path%20for%20FB%20longer%20term.%26quot%3B%20Nothing%20like%20a%20little%20sibling%20rivalry.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-facebook-losing-cultural-relevancy-mark-zuckerberg-emails-ftc-trial-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744921307000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68015f0fa466d2b74ab38179%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-facebook-losing-cultural-relevancy-mark-zuckerberg-emails-ftc-trial-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Emails%20presented%20during%20the%20Meta's%20FTC%20antitrust%20trial%20reveal%20Mark%20Zuckerberg's%20worries%20about%20Facebook.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22sbradley%40insider.com%20(Sydney%20Bradley)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A82%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-facebook-losing-cultural-relevancy-mark-zuckerberg-emails-ftc-trial-2025-4%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl