0revenue%20of%20between%20%2443.5%20billion%20and%20%2444.5%20billion%20for%20the%20year%2C%20as%20well%20as%20an%20operating%20margin%20of%2029%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-biggest-quarter-new-subscribers-ever-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENetflix%20has%20added%20more%20new%20subscribers%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20analysts%20expected%20in%20recent%20quarters%2C%20in%20part%20thanks%20to%20new%20policies%20aimed%20at%20reducing%20password%20sharing.%20That's%20pushed%20many%20who%20might%20have%20been%20using%20credentials%20from%20a%20friend%20or%20family%20member%20to%20start%20paying%20for%20their%20own%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarting%20with%20Thursday's%20report%2C%20though%2C%20Netflix%20is%20no%20longer%20providing%20quarterly%20updates%20on%20how%20many%20new%20subscribers%20it%20logged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20streaming%20land%20grab%20era%20is%20dead%20for%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ross%20Benes%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20Business%20Insider's%20sister%20company%2C%20EMARKETER%2C%20after%20the%20company%20reported%20earnings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNetflix%20got%20ahead%20of%20the%20story%20by%20eliminating%20its%20quarterly%20subscriber%20update%20just%20as%20password%20sharing%20gains%20were%20set%20to%20decline%20and%20the%20outlook%20on%20subscriber%20increases%20appeared%20stale%2C%26quot%3B%20Benes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20Wall%20Street%20analysts%20were%20looking%20for%20details%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-earnings-what-wall-street-looking-at-after-subscription-data-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ead%20sales%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20well%20as%20Netflix's%20plans%20for%20sports%20and%20creator%20content%20to%20judge%20how%20the%20company%20is%20doing.%20Netflix%20co-CEO%20Ted%20Sarandos%20said%20Thursday%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-video-podcasts-could-come-t