20database.%26quot%3B%20Connolly%20said%20the%20Committee%20has%20information%20that%20indicates%20DOGE%20%26quot%3Bis%20carrying%20out%20its%20work%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20disregards%20important%20cybersecurity%20and%20privacy%20considerations%2C%20potentially%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20law.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConnolly%20said%20that%20DOGE%20engineers%20have%20tried%20to%20skirt%20network%20security%20controls%20to%20create%20specialized%20computers%20for%20themselves%20with%20full%20access%20to%20data%20across%20agencies%2C%20and%20that%20DOGE%20associates%20have%20been%20collecting%20%26quot%3Bbackpacks%20full%20of%20laptops%26quot%3B%20each%20containing%20access%20to%20federal%20agencies'%20databases.%20Such%20actions%20could%20be%20in%20violation%20of%20federal%20laws%20that%20limit%20how%20agencies%20share%20information%20with%20each%20other%20and%20that%20require%20individuals'%20consent%20before%20such%20information%20is%20shared%2C%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20of%20Connolly's%20concerns%20is%20the%20recent%20staffing%20reductions%20at%20the%20SSA%20and%20the%20impact%20on%20IT%20systems.%20On%20top%20of%20already%20eliminating%20around%207%2C000%20positions%20at%20the%20SSA%2C%20DOGE%20has%20called%20for%20cutting%2050%25%20of%20the%20technology%20staff%20that%20manage%20the%20agency's%20website%2C%20benefits%20portals%2C%20and%20IT%20systems%2C%20Connolly%20wrote%2C%20citing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2F2025%2F04%2F07%2Fsocial-security-website-crashes-musk-trump%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%2C%20Connolly%20said%2C%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20plans%20to%20eliminate%20an%20additional%2025%25%20of%20staffers%20who%20oversee%20the%20SSA's%20data%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20mass%20firings%20are%20happening%20at%20the%20same%20time%20the%20SSA%20has%20experienced%20repeated%20IT%20failures%20and%20website%20outages%2C%20which%