%23%3A~%3Atext%3D%2527-%2CThe%2520scheme%2520provides%2520for%2520a%2520subsidy%2520of%252060%2525%2520of%2520the%2C3%2520kW%2520systems%2520or%2520higher.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPM%20Surya%20Ghar%20Muft%20Bijli%20Yojana%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20government%20currently%20covers%2060%20percent%20of%20the%20solar%20unit%20cost%20for%20systems%20up%20to%202%20kW%2C%20and%2040%20percent%20for%20systems%20between%202%20and%203%20kW.%20The%20subsidy%20is%20capped%20at%203%20kW%20with%20a%20maximum%20benefit%20of%20Rs%2078%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuneet%20sees%20the%20current%20framework%20as%20limiting.%20He%20believes%20it%20needs%20to%20evolve%20so%20that%20larger%20solar%20systems%20can%20also%20become%20affordable%20%E2%80%94%20without%20depending%20too%20much%20on%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20current%20system%20offers%20subsidies%20only%20up%20to%203%20kW%2C%20but%20an%20energy%20consumption%20level%20of%203%20kW%20is%20minimal.%20These%20subsidies%20are%20helpful%20for%20those%20below%20the%20poverty%20line%2C%20but%20not%20for%20others%2C%20who%20may%20need%20more%20capacity%2C%20like%20young%20entrepreneurs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2Fsolar-startups-3-1744896621.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Suneet%20advocates%20for%20off-grid%20systems%20with%20energy%20storage.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2Fsolar-startups-3-1744896621.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2Fsolar-startups-3-1744896621-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2Fsolar-startups-3-1744896621-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2Fsolar-startups-3-1744896621-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F04%2Fsolar-startups-3-1744896621-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-421354%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESuneet%20advocates%20for%20off-grid%20systems%20with%20energy%20storage.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%20that%20middle%20and%20upper-middle-class%20consumers%20may%20not%20find%20the%20scheme%20attractive%20if%20their%20solar%20rooftop%20investment%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20translate%20into%20significant%20cost%20savings.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20who%20understand%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%203%20kW%20scheme%20will%20likely%20look%20for%20other%20options.%20The%20next%20level%20of%20subsidy%20is%20at%2010%20kW%2C%20but%20the%20rate%20drops%20considerably%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20systems%20up%20to%2010%20kW%2C%20homeowners%20and%20housing%20societies%20are%20eligible%20for%20Rs%209%2C000-%20Rs%2018%2C000%20per%20kW%20for%20installing%20rooftop%20solar%20systems.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20current%20subsidy%20scheme%20effectively%20reduces%20costs%20for%20small%20solar%20setups%2C%20but%20not%20for%20larger%20projects.%20Offering%20better%20loan%20terms%20or%20insurance%20support%20for%20solar%20installations%20could%20have%20a%20longer-lasting%20impact%20than%20just%20direct%20subsidies%2C%E2%80%9D%20Suneet%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E7.%20Ensure%20equitable%20electricity%20access%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETanveer%20highlights%20another%20critical%20gap%3A%20current%20systems%20require%20a%20minimum%20number%20of%20households%20to%20justify%20extending%20the%20grid%2C%20which%20leaves%20many%20small%20villages%20without%20power.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20a%20village%20has%20fewer%20households%20than%20required%2C%20they%20are%20not%20provided%20with%20a%20grid%20connection.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20these%20smaller%20communities%20are%20left%20in%20the%20dark%20for%20extended%20periods.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20points%20out%20that%20electricity%20needs%20in%20rural%20areas%20vary%20widely.%20Farmers%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20require%20more%20power%20to%20operate%20electric%20motors%20for%20irrigation%2C%20while%20migrant%20labourers%20may%20only%20need%20electricity%20for%20basic%20needs%20like%20lights%20or%20fans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CReforms%20should%20ensure%20wider%20accessibility%20regardless%20of%20village%20size%20and%20account%20for%20the%20diverse%20electricity%20needs%20of%20different%20occupational%20groups%20in%20rural%20areas%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tanveer%20says.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20must%20ensure%20access%20to%20electricity%20is%20tailored%20to%20their%20needs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E8.%20Training%20and%20capacity%20building%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEducation%20programmes%20on%20maintaining%20solar%20systems%20are%20vital.%20Tanveer%20notes%20that%20simply%20donating%20these%20systems%2C%20without%20equipping%20people%20with%20the%20skills%20to%20use%20and%20care%20for%20them%2C%20often%20results%20in%20neglect%20and%20inefficiencies.%20Developing%20local%20technician-training%20initiatives%20can%20empower%20communities%20to%20maintain%20their%20own%20systems%20and%20reduce%20long-term%20dependency%20on%20outside%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E9.%20Encouraging%20CSR%20initiatives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGreater%20involvement%20of%20CSR%20(corporate%20social%20responsibility)%20initiatives%20in%20solar%20projects%20can%20elevate%20their%20impact.%20These%20reforms%2C%20Tanveer%20says%2C%20should%20focus%20on%20engaging%20with%20community-centric%20solutions%20that%20not%20only%20address%20energy%20supply%20but%20also%20uplift%20the%20socio-economic%20conditions%20of%20rural%20populations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20reforms%20could%20broaden%20access%20to%20solar%20energy%20and%20facilitate%20t